@startuml
!theme plain
autonumber

actor "Port Authority Officer" as Officer
participant "User Interface\n(UI)" as UI
box "Backend System (Sistema AIT)" #LightBlue
    participant "HTTP Request" as HttpRequest
    participant "Route" as Route
    participant "VesselController" as Controller
    participant "VesselDto" as Dto
    participant "IVesselService\n(Service)" as Service
    participant "IVesselRepository\n(Repository)" as Repository
end box

Officer -> UI : 1: create or update vessel data
activate UI

UI -> HttpRequest : 1.1: POST /api/vessel OR PUT /api/vessel/{imo} \n (VesselCreateDto / VesselDto)
activate HttpRequest
HttpRequest -> Route : 1.2: Match Route
activate Route
Route -> Controller : 1.3: Invoke CreateVessel / UpdateVessel
activate Controller

Controller -> Dto : 1.3.1: Map DTO from request body
activate Dto
Dto --> Controller : 1.3.2: Mapped DTO
deactivate Dto

Controller -> Service : 1.4: CreateVesselAsync / UpdateVesselAsync (VesselDto)
activate Service

Service -> Repository : 1.4.1: AddAsync / UpdateAsync (Vessel entity)
activate Repository
Repository --> Service : 1.4.2: Vessel entity persisted
deactivate Repository

Service --> Controller : 1.5: VesselDto (created/updated)
deactivate Service

Controller --> HttpRequest : 1.6: HTTP 201 Created / 200 OK (VesselDto)
deactivate Controller
deactivate Route
deactivate HttpRequest

HttpRequest --> UI : 1.7: HTTP Response
deactivate UI

UI --> Officer : 1.8: Display confirmation / new data

@enduml